Only accessible from the home session
-------------------------------------

+ DONE func makeAppRoute(appHash) securityCode
    So the input should be {apphash: <base64 encoded 32-byte hash>}
    And the response is a unicode-encoded random string.
+ DONE func getApp()
    Request to localhost:3000/getapp/securityCode
+ DONE func saveApp() appHash
+ DONE func sendApp(appHash, recipients [][]byte)
+ DONE func searchApps(tags []string, searchString string) metadata
+ func viewApp(hash string) (200 OK)
	"""
	1. generate a security code
	2. make a directory in 'tmp' with a randomly generated name
	3. untar the app into the temporary directory
	4. put the mapping from security code to temporary directory name in the state
	5. when a request comes in to viewapp/securityCode/filename, then serve it up


